description:
Less than siblings, more than friends.

Kajitsu has never known a proper family. Her dad’s a deadbeat and her mom changes husbands like most people change socks. Kaijitsu isn’t alone in her dysfunction--Taro and Natsu, the hottie step brothers she hasn’t seen in seven years, are also refugees from negligent parents in search of a home. Abandoned by everyone but each other, the three not-quite-siblings make one last attempt at building a family. It’s hard enough getting along in a home with rampant hormones and no adults, but when an unexpected bundle of joy is dropped in their laps, can they learn to be parents, too?

Contents

  • Chapter 1: In the Wind
  • Chapter 2: Crossroad
  • Chapter 3: Thank You
  • Chapter 4: The Letter
  • Chapter 5: No Incest Allowed!
  • Bonus Comic 1
  • Bonus Comic 2
name: Vol. 1

description:
Life in a house with no grown-ups seems to be doing wonders for Kajitsu. For the first time in her life, she has a best friend, and to everyone's surprise, she's taken an interest in boys. Too bad her crush is on the new Calligraphy teacher Akai-sensei!

Things aren't going quite as well for her step-brother and classmate Natsu. As the smartest kid in school, his teachers hope he'll boost the school's sagging reputation by getting into Japan's top university - no pressure!

And Natsu still hasn't come to terms with the tragic events that took away the gentle smile that Kajitsu so loved. What happened to him in those years apart?

Contents

  • Chapter 6: Mother
  • Chapter 7: My Make-Over Project
  • Chapter 8: Natsu's Memories (Pt. 1)
  • Chapter 9: Natsu's Memories (Pt. 2)
  • Chapter 10: Rhapsody of Youth
  • Chapter 11: The Greatest Love in the World
  • Bonus Comic 1
  • Bonus Comic 2
  • Bonus Comic 3
name: Vol. 2

description:
Life in the Toda household is getting more complicated by the minute! With no parental figure to control her dating habits, Kajitsu finds herself on a romantic evening out with her favorite teacher, Akai-sensei, secretly hoping he'll make her forget the one boy she can't have!

Meanwhile, her dearest step-brother Natsu is faced with the temptation of opening her private diary. Will he expose Kajitsu's deepest fantasies about him?

Contents

  • Chapter 12: The Naked Night
  • Chapter 13: Short-Sleeves
  • Chapter 14: Your Blue (Part One)
  • Chapter 15: Your Blue (Part Two)
  • Chapter 16: A Morning in the Toda Household
  • Bonus Manga: Sneak Attack!! Onii-chan Takes the Scene!!

  • Bonus Manga: Satsuki-chan's Record of Struggles 2
  • Bonus Manga: Cha-cha-cha and Shake it Shake it
  • Bonus Manga: Shioko Afterward
name: Vol. 3

description:
Less than siblings, more than friends...

The Toda household continues its epic struggle against a cruel world that threatens to tear it apart! Kajitsu trembles on the threshold of womanhood when her teacher offers to tutor her in more than just calligraphy. Meanwhile her beloved step-brother Natsu is showing all the signs of being in love with a really hot girl! And elder brother Taro is skimming money from the household funds! Is he the father of a love child, or is there an even shadier reason for his behavior?

Contents

  • Chapter 17: Door
  • Chapter 18: Scent
  • Chapter 19: Onii-chan
  • Chapter 20: Calling
  • Chapter 21: Key
name: Vol. 4

description:
Less than siblings, more than friends...

Still reeling from the discovery of Natsu and Erica's relationship, the distraught Kajitsu runs away from home -- straight into the arms of Akai-sensei! As if moving in with her teacher wasn't risky enough, Kajitsu finally loses her temper when Erica continues to challenge Natsu about his feelings for his sister! Can love survive when Kajitsu's secret living arrangement and Erica's interference threaten to tear the fragile Toda family circle apart?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 22: Inside the Box 1
  • Chapter 23: Inside the Box 2
  • Chapter 24: Inside the Box 3
  • Chapter 25: Inside the Box 4
  • Chapter 26: Inside the Box 5
name: Vol. 5

description:
Less than siblings, more than friends...

Summer's in full sway; it's hot outside... and even hotter inside. Kajitsu has to make the most important decision in her life about Akai-sensei. Meanwhile, her arch-rival Erica's relationship with Natsu takes an unexpected turn -- one that could throw feul on the fire of Natsu's and Kajitsu's own forbidden feelings!

Contents

  • Chapter 27: Confession
  • Chapter 28: When a Boy Cuts His Hair
  • Chapter 29: Summer and Fevers
  • Chapter 30: Until Dawn
  • Girlfriend Only for Graduation Trip
name: Vol. 6

description:
Less than siblings, more than friends...

The climax is at hand! The emotional storms battering the Toda household come to a head when Rumiko's meddling forces Taro and Natsu into a violent confrontation. Will Taro grant permission to Natsu and Kajitsu to date, or will this mean an end to the Toda family? Distraught, Kajitsu turns to Akai-sensei for comfort -- only to be given shocking news! All this and more in the life-changing final volume of Crossroad!

Contents

  • Chapter 31: Remnants of a Dream
  • Chapter 32: Missing
  • Chapter 33: Light
  • Last Chapter: Far Away
  • After a Broken Heart
name: Vol. 7

description: Once upon a time, Archer Coe was a neophyte hypnotist working at a dingy nightclub and pulling short cons. Long before his troubles with the police and the mysterious murder of Jack Midland, Archer was a key performer in an entirely different reality. Who are the other players in this forgotten mystery, and how did it get Archer Coe into the pickle that's currently threatening to drive him mad?

description: Jonathan Harker is called to Transylvania to facilitate a London estate purchase by Count Dracula. But when Harker finds himself a prisoner in the castle of Dracula and three beautiful women threaten him, he realizes that this is no simple business transaction. His only hope is to escape or die because the alternative is unthinkable to him. Presenting a faithful adaption of Bram Stoker's classic horror literary tale.
